<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9260] Threadpool in RepairSession is not shutdown on failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9260</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are not closing taskExecutor in RepairSession if any RepairJob fails. The only way it will close is if a replica goes down and shutdown is called via IFailureDetectionEventListener. &lt;br/&gt;
If RepairJob fails due to say snapshot timing out, C* will not call shutdown on this pool. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
